For a complete description of use custom fonts in client-side, read the article: Custom fonts (client-side) &gt; via Virtual file system (VFS)
If you don&rsquo;t want to install gulp and/or just downloaded pdfMake and want to use custom fonts in client-side, you can generate the vfs_fonts.js with an bash-script as well:
#!/bin/sh  if [ -t 1 ]; then target=&#34;vfs_fonts.js&#34; else target=&#34;/dev/stdout&#34; fi ( echo &#34;var vfs = {&#34; for file in &#34;$@&#34;; do file=$1 filename=$(basename $file) filecontent=$(base64 -w 0 $file) shift echo &#34;\&#34;${filename}\&#34;:\&#34;${filecontent}\&#34;&#34; if [ &#34;$#&#34; -gt 0 ]; then echo &#34;,&#34; fi done echo &#34;}&#34; echo &#34;; var _global = typeof window === &#39;object&#39; ?

